WEBVTT

00:04.960 --> 00:06.840
you've had a crutch to lean on.

00:06.840 --> 00:09.160
I swear in the name
of Almighty God,

00:09.160 --> 00:11.480
I will take revenge on
Tommy Shelby.

00:11.480 --> 00:14.320
That, my friend,
is the finest opium in the world.

00:14.320 --> 00:17.920
Perhaps we can meet after you've
spoken with your wife's uncle,
Jack Nelson.

00:17.920 --> 00:20.640
Tommy Shelby wants
to do business with Jack Nelson?

00:20.640 --> 00:22.680
So, speak to your uncle
and get me out of here.

00:22.680 --> 00:24.320
If he doesn't want to buy my opium,

00:24.320 --> 00:26.360
I will sell to the
East Boston Jews.

00:26.360 --> 00:28.200
It's Ruby. She's not well.

00:28.200 --> 00:29.320
I'm coming home.

00:29.320 --> 00:35.200
This programme contains
strong language

00:35.200 --> 00:39.480
There will be a war in this
family and one of you will die.

00:41.160 --> 00:44.480
You've been too busy to
punish the people that killed her.

00:44.480 --> 00:46.200
How is the family?

00:57.520 --> 00:58.680
Daddy.

01:03.120 --> 01:04.440
Hello, Ruby.

01:05.640 --> 01:07.000
Come here.

01:07.000 --> 01:08.080
Let me see you.

01:09.240 --> 01:12.200
I missed you. I missed you.

01:13.280 --> 01:14.960
That is a Black Madonna.

01:14.960 --> 01:16.760
What presents did you get us, Dad?

01:16.760 --> 01:18.200
Son.

01:18.200 --> 01:19.760
She's all better, Tommy.

01:19.760 --> 01:21.160
You came back for nothing.

01:25.400 --> 01:26.880
But I'm glad you're back.

01:28.920 --> 01:30.920
Right, before we do anything else,

01:30.920 --> 01:33.400
we're going to go for a drive, OK?

01:33.400 --> 01:34.920
Let's go. What about me?

01:34.920 --> 01:36.440
Yeah, you can come too, come on.

01:36.440 --> 01:38.320
A drive where?

01:38.320 --> 01:40.960
I've asked the driver to take
us to see Dr Robert.

01:40.960 --> 01:43.640
I want him to have a look at Ruby.
Why, love?

01:43.640 --> 01:46.840
The appointment is in one hour,
you can stay here or you can come.

01:48.200 --> 01:50.040
Right.

01:50.040 --> 01:51.920
Right, let's go.

02:30.000 --> 02:33.560
TOMMY GRUNTS AND RETCHES

02:33.560 --> 02:36.280
HE COUGHS

02:41.920 --> 02:43.760
Tommy?

02:43.760 --> 02:44.960
Yeah?

02:47.160 --> 02:49.360
It was all good.
Everything was clear.

02:50.920 --> 02:52.120
That is a relief.

02:53.320 --> 02:55.960
That's a relief.
Yeah.

02:55.960 --> 02:57.400
Driver's bringing the car round.

02:57.400 --> 02:58.840
TAP ON WINDOW
Daddy.

03:00.440 --> 03:01.680
Hiya.

03:04.960 --> 03:06.000
Come here.

03:12.400 --> 03:13.920
When did you last sleep?

03:16.040 --> 03:18.280
Not much since we last spoke
on the phone.

03:19.320 --> 03:22.560
Well, now you know Ruby's all clear,
you can sleep.

03:22.560 --> 03:24.120
Yeah.

03:26.240 --> 03:29.680
Lizzie, I am very happy that
Ruby's results are clear.

03:29.680 --> 03:31.120
But still you won't sleep.

03:32.800 --> 03:36.160
I will speak to Johnny
and I will speak to Esmeralda.

03:36.160 --> 03:38.240
LIZZIE SIGHS

03:41.880 --> 03:43.160
We could be on holiday.

03:44.200 --> 03:46.040
We could be up a mountain
in America.

03:47.080 --> 03:48.840
That wouldn't have been possible.

03:49.880 --> 03:53.720
The man I'm dealing with is coming
to London. I need to be there.

03:55.240 --> 03:56.360
No escape.

03:58.040 --> 04:01.800
We will escape, Lizzie.
One last deal to be done.

04:01.800 --> 04:04.880
It'll be difficult.
Difficulties are to be expected.

04:04.880 --> 04:07.840
This is why I must move
from item to item.

04:12.880 --> 04:14.080
Do you feel that?

04:15.280 --> 04:16.680
Do you feel anything?

04:18.040 --> 04:21.640
You know, you talk as if you're
watching everything on a screen.

04:25.480 --> 04:27.800
When we go home. When we go home,

04:27.800 --> 04:31.000
we'll give the kids to Frances,
and then you and me will go to bed.

04:32.960 --> 04:34.840
And I will be the next item.

04:34.840 --> 04:37.840
That's how it feels now, Tommy.
Yeah.

04:37.840 --> 04:39.080
Everything on a list.

04:45.800 --> 04:48.200
Hey, baby.
When are we going home?

04:53.320 --> 04:55.240
THUNDER ROARS

04:57.120 --> 05:00.320
LOUD THUD
GLASS SHATTERS

05:08.200 --> 05:10.400
Tommy? Tommy?

05:11.800 --> 05:14.040
MEN GRUNT

05:18.160 --> 05:20.600
DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS

05:22.960 --> 05:25.240
Tommy? What's happened?

05:26.360 --> 05:27.800
Fuck, fuck.

05:28.920 --> 05:30.120
Fuck.

05:31.800 --> 05:33.760
Tommy. Come here. Come here.

05:33.760 --> 05:34.960
What's happened?

05:37.480 --> 05:38.760
Tommy.

05:41.160 --> 05:43.640
MUSIC STOPS

05:43.640 --> 05:45.600
TOMMY BREATHES

06:01.160 --> 06:02.400
It is four years...

06:04.360 --> 06:06.120
..one month and six days

06:06.120 --> 06:07.320
since I had a drink.

06:09.160 --> 06:11.000
My head is clear.

06:12.480 --> 06:13.920
I am myself.

06:16.480 --> 06:17.680
Is this the first time?

06:20.080 --> 06:22.480
Once on the ship back. Not as bad.

06:24.840 --> 06:26.400
Tommy...

06:27.960 --> 06:29.480
..you need to see a doctor.

06:31.480 --> 06:33.080
I've work to do.

06:35.680 --> 06:37.200
It's the work that's to blame.

06:38.240 --> 06:40.120
The people you meet,
the lies that you tell.

06:42.960 --> 06:45.920
We're going to keep going till
the Boston business is done.

06:47.200 --> 06:48.240
Then we rest.

06:49.880 --> 06:51.960
Then we Peaky Blinders fucking rest.

06:56.560 --> 06:59.840
Comrades, before we
end this planning meeting

06:59.840 --> 07:02.240
and send you out into the rain...
LIGHT CHUCKLES

07:02.240 --> 07:03.680
..we have a surprise.

07:05.000 --> 07:08.320
He just arrived back from
a trade mission to America.

07:08.320 --> 07:09.680
He came back early

07:09.680 --> 07:12.920
and he has insisted on addressing
you volunteers in person.

07:14.080 --> 07:15.680
Comrades,

07:15.680 --> 07:17.880
your Labour representative
for South Birmingham,

07:17.880 --> 07:20.480
Mr Thomas Shelby MP, OBE.
RAUCOUS CHEERING

07:44.920 --> 07:49.320
I bring with me on
the train from London...

07:50.480 --> 07:52.840
..a message from Westminster.

07:54.440 --> 07:57.920
No. No, no, no, not a message.

07:57.920 --> 07:58.960
Not a message.

08:00.640 --> 08:02.640
An instruction, in fact.

08:02.640 --> 08:04.880
CROWD MURMURS

08:04.880 --> 08:08.520
You must be silent.
CROWD MUMBLES IN DISAGREEMENT

08:11.200 --> 08:12.720
You must say nothing.

08:14.760 --> 08:18.120
Say nothing about the present
situation in this city.

08:20.040 --> 08:22.040
Say nothing about hunger.

08:22.040 --> 08:24.120
Say nothing about jobs.

08:24.120 --> 08:26.640
Say nothing about pay.

08:26.640 --> 08:29.520
But those in greener pastures,

08:29.520 --> 08:32.640
they may speak.
CROWD MURMURS

08:32.640 --> 08:35.560
They may raise their voices.
CROWD YELLS INDISTINCTLY

08:35.560 --> 08:38.120
But here in the smoke,
you men and women,

08:38.120 --> 08:39.920
Irish and Italian

08:39.920 --> 08:43.080
and English who support
the Socialist cause...

08:44.120 --> 08:46.440
And even your socialist cats and
dogs and canaries.

08:46.440 --> 08:48.600
CROWD LAUGHS

08:48.600 --> 08:50.760
..you must hush.

08:50.760 --> 08:55.560
Because the King, and all the King's
horses and all the King's men...

08:55.560 --> 08:57.080
CROWD CHUCKLES

08:57.080 --> 08:59.280
..want you to be silent.

08:59.280 --> 09:02.240
But it is you, my friends,
who must suffer

09:02.240 --> 09:06.080
the cuts in wages and
in welfare and in dignity.

09:06.080 --> 09:07.840
And you must not complain,

09:07.840 --> 09:10.440
because that would be unpatriotic.

09:10.440 --> 09:13.560
You soldiers,
who have fought in France,

09:13.560 --> 09:15.760
you are traitors if you speak up.

09:15.760 --> 09:20.240
You veterans of their wars
and their booms and their busts,

09:20.240 --> 09:22.560
it is you who must take the blows,

09:22.560 --> 09:25.800
and carry the burdens
for the sake of those

09:25.800 --> 09:28.200
in greener pastures who
bellow at you...

09:28.200 --> 09:30.280
HE SLAMS HAND

09:30.280 --> 09:31.560
.."Silence".

09:31.560 --> 09:33.480
CROWD YELLS IN DISSENT

09:33.480 --> 09:35.320
Well, watch this, comrades.

09:35.320 --> 09:36.960
I will not be silent.

09:38.280 --> 09:39.600
Not this Englishman.

09:39.600 --> 09:41.520
CROWD CHEERS

09:47.320 --> 09:49.160
No silence from me.

09:49.160 --> 09:51.080
No silence from me,

09:51.080 --> 09:54.760
because I have heard your voices
when you come to me

09:54.760 --> 09:58.200
and tell me about
the cries of your hungry children,

09:58.200 --> 10:02.160
and I will gather up every
single one of those cries

10:02.160 --> 10:06.160
and I will take 'em with me
on the train to Westminster...

10:06.160 --> 10:08.080
CROWD CHEERS

10:08.080 --> 10:10.480
..and I will let them out
of the bag in the House of Commons,

10:10.480 --> 10:12.560
and let them
try to silence that, eh?

10:12.560 --> 10:14.440
CROWD CHEERS

10:25.160 --> 10:27.120
TOMMY SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY

10:29.600 --> 10:32.520
Shouldn't that involve
some sharing of the burden?

10:34.000 --> 10:36.360
All of us taking
a smaller slice of the cake, eh?

10:37.520 --> 10:40.280
After all, it's bloody us
who bakes the cake

10:40.280 --> 10:43.920
and makes the cars
and melts the metal.

10:43.920 --> 10:46.840
And the King, remember him,

10:46.840 --> 10:49.560
the man who ordered all of this,

10:49.560 --> 10:52.640
shouldn't he be taking
some of the cuts?

10:52.640 --> 10:54.560
Eh, some of the blows?

10:54.560 --> 10:57.440
Some of the pain? No or yes?

10:57.440 --> 10:59.160
YES!

11:10.000 --> 11:11.520
Hush.

11:11.520 --> 11:14.000
Hush, you working men and women.

11:14.000 --> 11:15.320
Silence.

11:18.240 --> 11:19.960
Good.

11:19.960 --> 11:21.280
Save your voices.

11:22.960 --> 11:27.000
You are going to need them on
Saturday when we rally together

11:27.000 --> 11:28.880
at the Bull Ring Market...

11:28.880 --> 11:30.320
CROWD CHEERS

11:30.320 --> 11:32.640
..and together,
we'll raise the roof,

11:32.640 --> 11:34.760
we'll break the damned silence...

11:37.280 --> 11:39.280
..and bring down this broken
government.

11:39.280 --> 11:41.680
CROWD CHEERS RAUCOUSLY

11:45.720 --> 11:47.840
Tommy, Tommy.

11:47.840 --> 11:49.840
Tommy, Tommy...

11:56.080 --> 11:57.120
Thank you.

11:59.680 --> 12:00.920
Laura McKee.

12:02.280 --> 12:05.480
Battalion Commander, Fermanagh IRA.

12:05.480 --> 12:07.760
You missed the first
and second act.

12:07.760 --> 12:09.320
Thank you for coming, Mr Shelby.

12:09.320 --> 12:10.640
Thank you. Thank you.

12:10.640 --> 12:11.920
The third act was enough.

12:14.640 --> 12:16.960
You both have reasons to hate me

12:16.960 --> 12:19.160
and to want to seek revenge
for the killing of...

12:19.160 --> 12:20.360
Sh.

12:22.000 --> 12:23.360
Gypsy tradition.

12:25.120 --> 12:29.400
We do not mention the name of
the dead in company.

12:34.520 --> 12:36.280
Laura McKee,

12:36.280 --> 12:38.080
in the Shelby family,

12:38.080 --> 12:41.560
business comes before issues
of vengeance.

12:41.560 --> 12:44.640
Our beloved departed would
understand and approve.

12:46.440 --> 12:48.120
Let's go, boys.

12:48.120 --> 12:50.440
Our agreement was we meet
in a crowded place.

12:50.440 --> 12:51.640
No need for crowds.

12:53.000 --> 12:54.040
We need you alive.

12:56.080 --> 12:57.560
After you.

13:21.840 --> 13:26.120
You know, Mr Shelby,
even though we've been doing
business for a while,

13:26.120 --> 13:27.920
we've never met in person.

13:29.000 --> 13:32.320
You spoke with passion
and compassion.

13:35.160 --> 13:37.600
You understand forgiveness

13:37.600 --> 13:39.200
and you drink water.

13:41.200 --> 13:44.120
Yet I heard from many reliable
sources

13:44.120 --> 13:48.040
that you have a reputation
for moral turpitude.

13:49.320 --> 13:51.280
TOMMY SNIFFS

13:51.280 --> 13:52.640
"Moral turpitude".

13:54.560 --> 13:56.200
It's a good name for a racehorse.

13:57.240 --> 13:58.720
You don't know what it means?

13:58.720 --> 14:00.840
I know what it means.

14:00.840 --> 14:02.400
It means you fuck people.

14:03.920 --> 14:06.440
Fuck people over. Don't give a fuck.

14:06.440 --> 14:08.040
It means you covet and steal

14:08.040 --> 14:11.080
and burn all principles
for the sake of self-interest.

14:13.320 --> 14:16.280
Well, I'm changing, Laura McKee,

14:16.280 --> 14:18.400
and my organisation
is also changing.

14:23.320 --> 14:25.000
So, what happened in Boston?

14:26.400 --> 14:28.480
Jack Nelson said no.

14:28.480 --> 14:31.440
Are we accepting "no" as an answer?

14:33.240 --> 14:36.560
These are letters written to

14:36.560 --> 14:39.240
and by Jack Nelson
over the last three months.

14:41.600 --> 14:44.320
TRAIN RUMBLES PAST

14:52.640 --> 14:53.760
This...

14:54.880 --> 14:58.160
This is a private letter from
the President of the United States.

14:59.480 --> 15:01.080
Where the fuck did you get this?

15:02.120 --> 15:04.600
My racehorse, Moral Turpitude,

15:04.600 --> 15:06.360
is just one of many in my stables.

15:07.400 --> 15:10.400
Sometimes even now I'll
take her out for a run,

15:10.400 --> 15:13.080
if there is a good cause that
requires her services.

15:17.960 --> 15:20.560
Jack Nelson's coming to London.

15:20.560 --> 15:24.800
Officially, he's coming
to buy liquor import licenses.

15:24.800 --> 15:28.600
Unofficially, he's on
a fact-finding mission.

15:28.600 --> 15:32.480
He's come to measure the strength of
support for fascism in Britain.

15:32.480 --> 15:34.320
He'll report back to the President.

15:37.160 --> 15:38.680
And how does that help us?

15:42.080 --> 15:44.200
In this letter to his son,

15:44.200 --> 15:47.920
Jack Nelson expresses
strong support for fascism.

15:47.920 --> 15:51.640
In this letter to a friend
in Berlin,

15:51.640 --> 15:55.640
he says some, erm,
interesting things about Jews.

15:58.120 --> 16:00.680
He's not coming to Europe
to find facts.

16:00.680 --> 16:03.360
He's coming to find proof
that fascism will prevail.

16:05.160 --> 16:08.840
And you and I are going
to help him in that task.

16:13.440 --> 16:15.040
I thought you were a socialist.

16:18.520 --> 16:20.400
Well...

16:20.400 --> 16:21.680
..since I've entered politics,

16:21.680 --> 16:24.200
I've learned that
the line doesn't go out from

16:24.200 --> 16:26.280
the middle to the left
and the right.

16:26.280 --> 16:27.880
It goes in a circle.

16:29.080 --> 16:30.120
I'll show you.

16:33.600 --> 16:35.920
You go far enough left,

16:35.920 --> 16:39.280
eventually you'll meet someone
who has gone far enough right

16:39.280 --> 16:40.920
to get to the same place.

16:43.720 --> 16:45.520
Working-class socialists like me,

16:45.520 --> 16:47.680
working-class nationalists like you.

16:47.680 --> 16:49.080
The result?

16:49.080 --> 16:50.680
National Socialism.

16:53.080 --> 16:55.040
And that's me,

16:55.040 --> 16:56.880
in the middle.

16:58.720 --> 17:02.720
Just a man trying to make an honest
living in a very dark world.

17:07.240 --> 17:10.120
You have friends in Dublin,
Laura McKee,

17:10.120 --> 17:13.360
who are actively fighting for
a Fascist Ireland.

17:13.360 --> 17:16.560
And you are acting on their behalf,
ain't you?

17:18.440 --> 17:21.520
When Jack Nelson comes to London,

17:21.520 --> 17:25.200
I can give him access
to Oswald Mosley

17:25.200 --> 17:28.720
and to Fascist sympathisers
in the House of Commons

17:28.720 --> 17:31.280
and the House of Lords,
on both sides of the divide.

17:32.920 --> 17:34.440
Fascism is quite the thing...

17:36.400 --> 17:37.920
..among the very best people.

17:39.560 --> 17:43.120
And with your help,
I can also offer him Dublin.

17:47.240 --> 17:51.680
And you think this will allow us
to ship our merchandise to Boston?

17:51.680 --> 17:53.480
Perhaps.

17:53.480 --> 17:56.920
There may be other
benefits for your cause.

17:58.080 --> 18:01.920
All you have to do
is sit with Jack Nelson

18:01.920 --> 18:05.200
and talk to him about a new
"golden age"

18:05.200 --> 18:07.800
and let him put a pin in
the map of Ireland

18:07.800 --> 18:09.760
for the President
of the United States.

18:11.200 --> 18:13.280
FOOTSTEPS APPROACH

18:20.320 --> 18:22.600
I came to collect
Arthur and put him to bed.

18:23.920 --> 18:26.840
I found him in the Garrison Lane
with a syringe in his hand.

18:26.840 --> 18:28.800
TOMMY SIGHS

18:32.720 --> 18:34.760
A friend loves at all times...

18:36.160 --> 18:39.240
..but a brother is born
for adversity.

18:39.240 --> 18:40.840
Proverbs 17, 17.

18:44.080 --> 18:48.000
I have two brothers in need,
but yours is the more urgent, Tommy.

18:48.000 --> 18:49.120
Will you come with me?

18:52.280 --> 18:53.640
So, Laura McKee...

18:54.960 --> 18:57.040
..are you going to help me
change the world?

18:59.320 --> 19:03.440
Mr Shelby, this meeting
is not what I expected.

19:03.440 --> 19:04.480
Never is.

19:05.480 --> 19:06.720
Is that a yes or a no?

19:09.520 --> 19:10.920
My answer's yes.

19:12.960 --> 19:14.520
The answer's always yes.

19:16.920 --> 19:19.720
The back door is unlocked.
You can let yourself out.

19:21.040 --> 19:23.000
And tell your friends back home,

19:23.000 --> 19:24.800
Tommy Shelby has changed.

19:31.400 --> 19:32.840
Where is he?

19:32.840 --> 19:34.720
When I found him,
the syringe was empty.

19:34.720 --> 19:36.680
He was sleeping it off
on the cobbles.

19:36.680 --> 19:38.240
Shit, Tommy. Shit.

19:39.280 --> 19:40.760
It's all under control, Ada.

19:40.760 --> 19:43.000
Well, I'm not under fucking control.

19:43.000 --> 19:47.720
I'm not you, Tommy,
and I'm not Polly either.

19:47.720 --> 19:49.280
Even though I'm trying to be.

19:49.280 --> 19:50.640
She would have stopped this.

19:50.640 --> 19:52.400
We will pull Arthur through this.

19:52.400 --> 19:54.880
I'm not talking about Arthur,
I'm talking about you.

19:54.880 --> 19:57.800
I heard everything
you were saying in there.

19:57.800 --> 20:00.440
Ada, this will be the end of it,
do you hear me?

20:00.440 --> 20:02.000
This is the way out for all of us.

20:02.000 --> 20:03.640
And along the way,
I will be doing good.

20:03.640 --> 20:06.480
No, along the way,
you're going to make yourself
a lot of fucking money.

20:06.480 --> 20:08.120
All right, fair enough.

20:08.120 --> 20:11.240
Any incidental rewards
for my good work will be welcome.

20:11.240 --> 20:13.440
But you will get
your fair share, sister.
SHE SCOFFS

20:13.440 --> 20:16.040
And by being among the Fascists,
by being among 'em,

20:16.040 --> 20:18.480
I can undermine them.

20:18.480 --> 20:19.880
Polly would approve.

20:21.280 --> 20:23.480
Beneath all the gold and diamonds,
and fucking,

20:23.480 --> 20:25.240
fucking mink and lace,

20:25.240 --> 20:26.600
she was a solid Socialist.

20:26.600 --> 20:28.480
TRAIN RUMBLES OVERHEAD

20:32.840 --> 20:35.320
Look, I know it's too late for this,
Tom, but...

20:37.000 --> 20:38.960
..this doorway,

20:38.960 --> 20:40.480
this same fucking doorway.

20:42.240 --> 20:44.720
We used to come here for Dad's beer

20:44.720 --> 20:47.440
and we were so little it took two
of us carry one bucket.

20:50.920 --> 20:52.160
Yeah, I remember.

20:56.080 --> 20:57.920
Look at us now, eh?

20:57.920 --> 20:59.240
Yeah.

20:59.240 --> 21:01.320
Fucking look at us.

21:01.320 --> 21:02.840
Take a good look, Tom,

21:02.840 --> 21:05.960
cos one of us isn't going
to be here for long.

