Our friend in Berlin doesn't either.

44:27.680 --> 44:29.520
They have that in common at least.

44:29.520 --> 44:31.960
Oh, I imagine they have lots
in common.

44:34.760 --> 44:37.520
Report to me, Shelby.

44:37.520 --> 44:40.920
Officially Jack Nelson is in London
to buy import licences.

44:44.040 --> 44:47.800
And unofficially,
he's Roosevelt's envoy.

44:47.800 --> 44:51.640
Well, as you can see from this
private letter,

44:51.640 --> 44:55.120
he is far from a neutral
point of view.

44:58.400 --> 45:00.880
Look at the bottom
of the second paragraph.

45:00.880 --> 45:04.840
"Individually Jews are fine
but as a race they stink."

45:04.840 --> 45:09.120
Hm. Elizabeth, do you even know
why the bridge

45:09.120 --> 45:12.000
to President Roosevelt
is so important?

45:14.520 --> 45:17.000
Actually, no.

45:17.000 --> 45:20.040
I don't really know much about this
business at all.

45:24.160 --> 45:27.120
But I have fucked
your future husband.

45:27.120 --> 45:29.160
So, I know lots of things about him.

45:31.600 --> 45:34.680
Tommy, I'll be outside.

45:34.680 --> 45:36.600
Well done, Elizabeth.

45:38.480 --> 45:40.440
TOMMY CLEARS THROAT

45:40.440 --> 45:44.040
Do you people want to meet Nelson
or no?

45:44.040 --> 45:47.640
Mr Shelby, from now on,
can I call you Thomas?

45:47.640 --> 45:49.200
If you like.

45:49.200 --> 45:50.680
Of course we would.

45:50.680 --> 45:53.520
And we are very grateful
for your efforts.

45:53.520 --> 45:58.320
But, Mr Shelby, before this
enterprise goes any further,

45:58.320 --> 46:01.320
you really must do
something about your wife.

46:28.840 --> 46:31.160
Mr Shelby.

46:31.160 --> 46:32.560
Yes.

46:32.560 --> 46:34.160
Mr Nelson.

46:34.160 --> 46:35.320
I came early.

46:36.760 --> 46:39.840
I wanted to come and take a look
around this beautiful church.

46:42.000 --> 46:44.040
You're Catholic, Mr Shelby.

46:45.360 --> 46:48.960
I hoped that by suggesting we meet
in church it might make us both

46:48.960 --> 46:53.400
more cautious with lies and truth.

46:53.400 --> 46:55.440
Well, your hope would be forlorn.

46:57.080 --> 47:00.520
There ain't no-one listening here.
You don't believe in God?

47:00.520 --> 47:02.240
No.

47:05.360 --> 47:07.640
It was the way Catholics were
treated in my country

47:07.640 --> 47:09.600
that made me angry.

47:10.880 --> 47:12.680
Made me what I became.

47:16.400 --> 47:18.880
What made you angry?

47:20.760 --> 47:23.720
Slowness in anything.

47:25.880 --> 47:28.840
I wanted to have everything already.

47:31.560 --> 47:34.000
Two working-class Catholic boys.

47:37.520 --> 47:40.920
Did they mess with you
when you were small?

47:40.920 --> 47:43.280
Some man in the shadows.

47:44.720 --> 47:47.240
I carried a screwdriver and a blade.

47:47.240 --> 47:50.960
And everyone believed
I had the power to lay curses.

47:50.960 --> 47:52.640
And do you?

47:52.640 --> 47:54.480
Yes, I do.

47:57.160 --> 47:59.640
First man I killed was a priest.

48:01.560 --> 48:03.920
You?

48:03.920 --> 48:08.120
A Prussian boy with green eyes,
he was already underground.

48:08.120 --> 48:10.720
When did you last kill a man,
Mr Shelby?

48:15.320 --> 48:16.720
Four years ago.

48:19.240 --> 48:22.520
His name was Tommy Shelby.

48:22.520 --> 48:23.560
He drank whisky.

48:26.480 --> 48:30.760
You want me to allow you
to enter my city

48:30.760 --> 48:33.360
and deal narcotics that will
kill people?

48:37.080 --> 48:39.960
You deal in whisky, Mr Nelson.

48:41.640 --> 48:44.680
I recently read a report
by the Vatican, actually,

48:44.680 --> 48:47.360
which said that whisky
disproportionately kills

48:47.360 --> 48:50.160
more of our Catholic brothers
and sisters,

48:50.160 --> 48:53.520
whereas opium is the sedative

48:53.520 --> 48:57.440
more often chosen
by Protestants and atheists.

49:00.080 --> 49:03.680
In return, there are people in
England who you think I should meet?

49:03.680 --> 49:06.480
Yes. Yes, like minds.

49:09.080 --> 49:12.960
I'm here to buy import licences
for booze.

49:14.840 --> 49:16.640
The booze of the blue blood elite.

49:18.120 --> 49:19.760
In America, we like...

49:19.760 --> 49:23.320
..we like labels and aspiration.

49:23.320 --> 49:27.800
Well, I have a brand of my own
vodka and gin.

49:27.800 --> 49:30.880
You can add that to your portfolio.

49:30.880 --> 49:34.280
I hear Shelby labels are favoured
by the working class.

49:34.280 --> 49:37.320
Indeed.
A fact of which I am very proud.

49:37.320 --> 49:40.800
They say you are a poet, too.

49:40.800 --> 49:43.000
No, I only read it.

49:45.040 --> 49:49.040
There are some people in this
country who I'd like to meet.

49:52.680 --> 49:53.920
Fascists.

49:53.920 --> 49:58.280
Not the ones in boots and black
shirts. The ones in tuxedos.

50:00.200 --> 50:02.800
I know men who are friends
of the cause.

50:02.800 --> 50:05.280
I also know men who are enemies
of the cause.

50:06.600 --> 50:07.840
For many years now,

50:07.840 --> 50:09.840
I have been working closely with
Winston Churchill,

50:09.840 --> 50:11.720
in many different capacities.

50:11.720 --> 50:14.040
I have his trust.

50:14.040 --> 50:16.440
He's opposed to the rise of fascism.

50:16.440 --> 50:19.360
You, I believe,
see it as inevitable.

50:21.120 --> 50:25.440
Well, I can give you men
of influence who support your cause.

50:25.440 --> 50:29.360
I can also offer you a full report
on Churchill's strategies.

50:33.000 --> 50:36.920
All this in return for access
to south Boston.

50:36.920 --> 50:38.680
Alternatively,

50:38.680 --> 50:41.200
you can take on Churchill
on your own,

50:41.200 --> 50:43.480
without my intelligence.

50:43.480 --> 50:45.960
And I can sell my opium to the Jews.

50:50.560 --> 50:52.960
You are a brave man, Mr Shelby.

50:54.520 --> 50:56.520
A war hero, I hear.

50:58.360 --> 51:00.640
Every war hero I ever met,
they're just someone

51:00.640 --> 51:02.720
who wanted to get themselves killed.

51:06.080 --> 51:08.560
Do we have a deal, Mr Nelson?

51:13.200 --> 51:16.120
I'll think a great deal about
what you've said.

51:29.560 --> 51:32.960
Ruby, have you finished
your spelling, love?

51:47.680 --> 51:49.520
Ruby?

51:50.800 --> 51:52.040
Ruby?

51:56.920 --> 51:58.840
Ruby?

52:03.040 --> 52:04.200
Ruby?

52:05.520 --> 52:07.720
What are you doing, love?

52:07.720 --> 52:10.560
I can hear voices.

52:10.560 --> 52:12.880
Coming from up the chimney.

52:16.160 --> 52:19.040
What voices? The grey man.

52:23.440 --> 52:26.560
Gentlemen, Mr Thomas Shelby.

52:26.560 --> 52:28.720
Birmingham South.

52:28.720 --> 52:31.040
THEY HECKLE

52:31.040 --> 52:32.240
Mr Speaker.

52:32.240 --> 52:33.880
I was raised in a family

52:33.880 --> 52:36.800
that endured living conditions
that would test

52:36.800 --> 52:40.040
the morality of even
the most virtuous.

52:40.040 --> 52:44.680
Indeed... Indeed, even the best of
us would have our virtues trounced

52:44.680 --> 52:47.240
and thwarted by life in the meanness

52:47.240 --> 52:50.240
and the bitterness of
an overcrowded British slum.

52:50.240 --> 52:52.680
What would you know about virtue?
THEY HECKLE

52:58.760 --> 53:01.160
Quickly, please.

53:02.600 --> 53:06.200
Therefore, Mr Speaker, I intend
to put before this House

53:06.200 --> 53:11.800
a bill which will offer radical
reform in housing in this country,

53:11.800 --> 53:15.720
in which slums are cleared
and new houses are built

53:15.720 --> 53:17.960
with new standards
in health and hygiene.

53:22.720 --> 53:26.600
Westminster 245. House of Commons.

53:26.600 --> 53:29.360
PHONE RINGS

53:30.680 --> 53:34.560
The time has come for change, the
people have had enough. They have!

53:34.560 --> 53:37.840
Let's open the windows,
let in new light,

53:37.840 --> 53:42.360
build a new Jerusalem
brick by Government-owned brick.

53:42.360 --> 53:44.640
THEY CHEER

53:48.200 --> 53:51.720
Into there.
SHE COUGHS

53:59.000 --> 54:01.320
Doctor?

54:04.360 --> 54:06.680
Yeah, Westminster 245.

54:10.880 --> 54:12.840
Mr Shelby.

54:31.480 --> 54:34.720
Tickner Maura O Beng,
O Beng over and over again.

54:34.720 --> 54:37.280
How is the family?
And one of you will die.

54:37.280 --> 54:40.840
They are staring at me, Daddy.
A man with green eyes.

54:40.840 --> 54:43.000
Can you stop the voices?

54:44.680 --> 54:47.400
There are no voices, my love.

54:47.400 --> 54:49.960
It's the grey man.

54:49.960 --> 54:52.360
He says he's coming for me...

54:53.400 --> 54:55.440
..and he's coming for Daddy as well.

55:07.640 --> 55:09.960
LOUD BLAST

55:09.960 --> 55:12.040
HE BREATHES HEAVILY

